The paper deals with a consensus problem in a network of agents, which is a classic topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The problem involves rational agents, which suggests a game-theoretic approach (cs.GT). The fairness property and the presence of coalitions also point towards social choice theory and mechanism design (cs.SI). The GOSSIP communication model is a specific type of network communication, which falls under the category of network protocols and algorithms (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes a randomized protocol with message complexity analysis, which is a typical topic in distributed algorithms (cs.DS).
